Description: Fragment of oval handle at neck join from a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium red-brown; grey core; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and oar symbol.
Type series: KT672 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Name Euphron. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 28a, 30
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0324)
